    public class MethodDeclaration
extends InstanceDeclaration
implements CallableMethod
    Declaration extension that represents the declaration of a method node type. See decodeStatement(Node, String, Location, boolean) for more details on what correct inputs look like.

      • getParameterList

        public ParameterList<Parameter> getParameterList()
        The the ParameterList that represents the parameters of the method.
        For example:
         public void methodName(int age, String name);
        In the previous statement, the data within the parenthesis are the parameters of the method. The ParameterList returned by this method would contain a node for each of the parameter specified, in the correct order from left to right.
        Specified by:
        getParameterList in interface CallableMethod
        Returns:
        The ParameterList that represents the parameters of the method.

      • getParameter

        public Parameter getParameter(int parameterIndex)
        Get the Parameter that the given index represents. The parameters are ordered from left to right, 0 being the first.

        For example: 
         public void run(int a, int b, int c)
 {
        ...
 }
        If you were to call getParameter(2) on the method above, you would receive the c Parameter.
        Parameters:
        parameterIndex - The index parameter to get.
        Returns:
        The Parameter at the given index.

      • setExternal

        public void setExternal(boolean external)
        Description copied from class: VariableDeclaration
        Set whether or not the variable is external. A variable is external if it is referenced from a language outside of Nova. For example, a variable from the C language. Furthermore, a variable is external if it begins with an externally imported C file's name.

        For example: 
         import "externalFile.h";
 
 ...
 
 public static void main(String args[])
 {
        // This is the external variable declaration.
        externalFile.externalType varName;
        
        // This is the external variable assignment.
        varName = externalFile.variableInstance;
 }
        In this example, 'externalFile' is the C header file that is imported. 'variableInstance' is the name of a variable that is contained within the imported header file.
        Overrides:
        setExternal in class VariableDeclaration
        Parameters:
        external - Whether or not the variable will be external.
        See Also:
        VariableDeclaration.setExternal(boolean)

      • decodeStatement

        public static MethodDeclaration decodeStatement(Node parent,
                                java.lang.String statement,
                                Location location,
                                boolean require)
        Decode the given statement into a Method instance, if possible. If it is not possible, this method returns null.
        Example inputs include:
        • public Person findPerson(String name, int age)
        • private int calculateArea(int width, int height)
        • public void doNothing()
        Parameters:
        parent - The parent node of the statement.
        statement - The statement to try to decode into a Method instance.
        location - The location of the statement in the source code.
        require - Whether or not to throw an error if anything goes wrong.
        Returns:
        The generated node, if it was possible to translated it into a Method.

      • interactWord

        public void interactWord(java.lang.String word,
                int wordNumber,
                Bounds bounds,
                int numWords,
                java.lang.String leftDelimiter,
                java.lang.String rightDelimiter,
                Node.ExtraData extra)
        Description copied from class: Node
        Method that is to be overridden. Whenever the iterateWords(String) method is called, this method will be called with the specific word and the number (order) the word came in the statement.
        Overrides:
        interactWord in class Node
        Parameters:
        word - The word that was found.
        wordNumber - The index of the word on a word-by-word basis.
        bounds - The bounds of the word that was found.
        numWords - The number of words that were parsed.
        leftDelimiter - The text that is between the previous word and the current word.
        rightDelimiter - The text that is between the current word and the next word.
        extra - The extra data that may or may not be needed for the interactWord() methods.
        See Also:
        Node.interactWord(java.lang.String, int, net.fathomsoft.nova.util.Bounds, int, java.lang.String, java.lang.String, net.fathomsoft.nova.tree.Node.ExtraData)
